SIMPLE: whereas
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whereas
<hw>Where*as"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>At which place;
where.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At last they came <qex>whereas</qex> that lady bode.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whereas</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whereas
<hw>Where*as"</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Considering that; it being the case that; since; --
used to introduce a preamble which is the basis of declarations,
affirmations, commands, requests, or like, that follow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>When in fact; while on the contrary; the case being
in truth that; although; -- implying opposition to something that
precedes; or implying recognition of facts, sometimes followed by a
different statement, and sometimes by inferences or something
consequent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Are not those found to be the greatest zealots who are most
notoriously ignorant? <qex>whereas</qex> true zeal should always begin
with true knowledge.</q> <rj><qau>Sprat.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whereat</ent>⟦br⟧
